I"u<p>A good city flag can provide a rallying point for civic pride and the template for the design code of a city. Just look to Chicago or Washington DC as examples. Unfortunately, in a TED Talk, Public Radio podcaster Roman Mars points out that most city flags are <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flag_of_Milwaukee">abominations</a> and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Cedar_rapids_flag.png">embarrassments</a>. While I was relieved that my home city of Minneapolis wasn’t on Mars’ worst list, I also couldn’t tell you what our flag looked like. Thats not good. A good flag will be flown.<!--more--></p>
